
The Proxy tool is used to monitor, analyze, and manipulate network traffic. It has the ability to capture, inspect, and modify requests and responses made over HTTP and HTTPS protocols. It is commonly used to identify security vulnerabilities.

The concept of a Proxy can be defined as a server that acts as an intermediary for communication between networked computers. 
It aims to protect users' privacy, enhance security, control access, and regulate network traffic while accessing the internet or other resources within the network. 
Proxies offer protection against security threats by hiding users' real IP addresses and filtering data traffic. They can also provide additional functions such as content filtering, access restrictions, and speed optimization.

